# Editorial Design Direction

Design is first-class for this app.

## Visual Language

- Prefer editorial, newspaper, and dossier-like composition.
- Use disciplined grids, large rectangular panels, mono labels, serif headlines, and publication-grade hierarchy.
- Preserve the homepage Section 03 / systems dossier language when extending related surfaces.
- Avoid generic SaaS card grids, interchangeable component-library layouts, and template aesthetics.

## UI Implementation

- Keep visual assets proportionate and integrated with the composition.
- Do not place visuals inside boxed content components if that makes them feel inserted rather than designed into the layout.
- Keep text fitting within containers across mobile and desktop.
- Use restrained motion and avoid decorative clutter.
- Use existing CSS naming and section patterns before inventing new ones.

## Content

- Keep professional Indonesian editorial language.
- Avoid inflated marketing copy.
- Preserve dr Ferdi Iskandar naming and medical profile tone unless Chief requests a content pivot.
